1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:06,381
[Ahmad] <i>From now on, you are</i>
<i>Police Major Allan Espina.</i>

2
00:00:06,464 --> 00:00:08,091
[suspenseful music playing]

3
00:00:08,174 --> 00:00:09,384
[Marcus] <i>Was that on purpose?</i>

4
00:00:09,467 --> 00:00:11,261
[Ahmad] <i>Marcus Reyes.</i>

5
00:00:11,344 --> 00:00:13,179
<i>They call him the best of the best.</i>

6
00:00:13,263 --> 00:00:17,475
<i>The one who led the raid on the island.</i>

7
00:00:17,559 --> 00:00:19,686
<i>I see you have met each other.</i>

8
00:00:19,769 --> 00:00:20,854
<i>This is Major Espina.</i>

9
00:00:20,937 --> 00:00:24,858
<i>He's the special liaison officer</i>
<i>sent by the Muslim Affairs.</i>

10
00:00:24,941 --> 00:00:26,693
<i>By the way, this is Agent Lara Angeles,</i>

11
00:00:26,776 --> 00:00:29,779
<i>the head agent of the task force.</i>

12
00:00:29,863 --> 00:00:32,365
<i>She is the brains and eyes</i>
<i>of all our operations.</i>

13
00:00:32,449 --> 00:00:34,284
[Lara] <i>Why can't I access your records?</i>

14
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:37,162
[Lara] <i>What are you hiding, Espina?</i>

15
00:00:37,245 --> 00:00:39,497
<i>What's your true motive?</i>

16
00:00:39,581 --> 00:00:42,375
<i>In other words, he can do as he pleases.</i>

17
00:00:42,459 --> 00:00:43,585
<i>Yeah, full access.</i>

18
00:00:43,668 --> 00:00:45,587
[Lara] <i>There's something wrong with</i>
<i>this. Shouldn't we act on it?</i>

19
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:47,338
<i>He's not even a part of our team!</i>

20
00:00:47,422 --> 00:00:50,049
[Jalil] <i>Facing the people who murdered</i>
<i>my neighbors</i>

21
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:52,010
<i>fills me with fury.</i>

22
00:00:52,093 --> 00:00:54,554
<i>I must see my mission through.</i>

23
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:58,099
<i>I will find the people</i>
<i>responsible for all of this.</i>

24
00:00:58,892 --> 00:01:00,602
<i>For Father.</i>

25
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:03,229
<i>For our neighbors.</i>

26
00:01:03,313 --> 00:01:04,814
[Marcus] <i>Why are you following me?</i>

27
00:01:05,356 --> 00:01:07,067
[grunts]

28
00:01:07,859 --> 00:01:09,360
[Marcus]
<i>I know you've been on my tail.</i>

29
00:01:09,444 --> 00:01:10,445
<i>What do you want from me?</i>

30
00:01:10,528 --> 00:01:11,988
I'm just doing my job.

31
00:01:12,072 --> 00:01:13,448
By keeping an eye on you.

32
00:01:13,531 --> 00:01:15,283
Not outside the office premises.

33
00:01:15,366 --> 00:01:17,535
Trouble always happens outside.

34
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:19,204
[Marcus] <i>Stop following me.</i>

35
00:01:20,330 --> 00:01:21,664
<i>I don't like being followed.</i>

36
00:01:21,748 --> 00:01:24,000
[suspenseful music playing]

37
00:01:25,084 --> 00:01:29,547
[theme music playing]

38
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:42,310
[crickets chirping]

39
00:01:42,393 --> 00:01:46,481
[gloomy music playing]

40
00:01:47,565 --> 00:01:49,192
[folder thudding]

41
00:01:52,737 --> 00:01:55,073
ARREST OF DATU RAHMAN LEADS TO MASSACRE

42
00:01:56,825 --> 00:02:01,704
[phone buzzing]

43
00:02:02,872 --> 00:02:04,457
- Brother.
- [Usman] <i>Brother.</i>

44
00:02:04,541 --> 00:02:06,751
So, are you on your way here?

45
00:02:06,835 --> 00:02:08,086
Someone was on my tail.

46
00:02:09,045 --> 00:02:10,130
I might get followed going there.

47
00:02:10,213 --> 00:02:12,006
- We have to be careful.
<i>- Copy.</i>

48
00:02:12,090 --> 00:02:13,758
I'll manage things here.

49
00:02:13,842 --> 00:02:15,135
Thank you, brother.

50
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:16,386
[gloomy music continues]

51
00:02:16,469 --> 00:02:18,221
[phone clatters]

52
00:02:31,943 --> 00:02:34,821
[gloomy music continues]

53
00:02:38,741 --> 00:02:40,160
- [line rings]
- [sighs]

54
00:02:40,243 --> 00:02:41,244
Buster.

55
00:02:41,911 --> 00:02:45,331
I need you to cross-reference
the initials "LDM."

56
00:02:46,291 --> 00:02:48,626
They appear in Datu Rahman's files.

57
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:50,044
[Buster] Alright, sir. I'll take a look.

58
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:53,423
[keyboard clacking]

59
00:02:55,758 --> 00:02:58,845
[gloomy music continues]

60
00:02:58,928 --> 00:03:01,431
[digital whirring]

61
00:03:01,514 --> 00:03:03,182
- [key clacks]
- [chiming]

62
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:07,061
Sir, it refers to Colonel Luis Del Mundo.

63
00:03:08,605 --> 00:03:09,814
Copy.

64
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:13,026
[phone thuds]

65
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:15,653
[keyboard clacking]

66
00:03:15,737 --> 00:03:17,655
[music intensifying]

67
00:03:18,489 --> 00:03:20,241
[Marcus] <i>I need to speak with you.</i>

68
00:03:20,825 --> 00:03:23,161
<i>Why would you accuse Datu Rahman?</i>

69
00:03:23,244 --> 00:03:24,495
<i>What do you know?</i>

70
00:03:25,288 --> 00:03:27,206
<i>What role did you play in this conspiracy?</i>

71
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:34,297
[pensive music playing]

72
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:43,806
[bowl thuds]

73
00:03:46,517 --> 00:03:48,394
[Omar] Jamilah, let's eat.

74
00:03:49,771 --> 00:03:50,688
Jamilah?

75
00:03:50,772 --> 00:03:51,689
Join us here.

76
00:03:51,773 --> 00:03:54,400
Look, I made some black soup.

77
00:03:54,484 --> 00:03:55,944
It's your favorite.

78
00:03:58,279 --> 00:03:59,948
It's alright, Auntie, Uncle.

79
00:04:00,031 --> 00:04:01,324
I'm still full.

80
00:04:03,743 --> 00:04:07,872
[phone buzzing]

81
00:04:12,252 --> 00:04:13,253
Hello?

82
00:04:14,128 --> 00:04:15,046
[Jalil] <i>Jamilah.</i>

83
00:04:15,129 --> 00:04:16,798
[somber music playing]

84
00:04:16,881 --> 00:04:17,882
Jalil?

85
00:04:18,508 --> 00:04:19,801
- Auntie!
- Is it Jalil?

86
00:04:19,884 --> 00:04:21,302
[Norhana in Arabic] Praise be to God!

87
00:04:22,804 --> 00:04:24,055
Jalil!

88
00:04:24,138 --> 00:04:26,307
[Omar] <i>Jalil, how are you?</i>

89
00:04:26,391 --> 00:04:29,185
Jalil, we're worried about you.

90
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:31,437
Jalil, what's going on?

91
00:04:32,063 --> 00:04:33,606
Where are you?

92
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:36,025
You haven't reached out
these past few days.

93
00:04:36,109 --> 00:04:38,111
I'm fine. Don't worry.

94
00:04:38,194 --> 00:04:39,654
[somber music continues]

95
00:04:39,737 --> 00:04:40,863
Jalil…

96
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:43,449
A video of our father is
making the rounds.

97
00:04:43,533 --> 00:04:44,701
Jamilah.

98
00:04:44,784 --> 00:04:46,744
You know Father couldn't have done that.

99
00:04:47,328 --> 00:04:49,580
But who's responsible for this?

100
00:04:49,664 --> 00:04:51,833
That's what I'm trying to find out.

101
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:55,128
You might get yourself in trouble, Jalil.

102
00:04:55,211 --> 00:04:57,714
[Omar] Jalil, what are you planning?

103
00:04:57,797 --> 00:04:59,424
[somber music continues]

104
00:04:59,507 --> 00:05:01,342
I can't say anything right now.

105
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:04,137
[Jalil] <i>So, Uncle, don't look for me.</i>

106
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:06,097
It's for your own safety.

107
00:05:07,098 --> 00:05:08,933
Okay, Jalil.

108
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:11,978
Just promise us that you'll be careful.

109
00:05:12,562 --> 00:05:13,855
[in Arabic] God willing.

110
00:05:14,981 --> 00:05:16,441
We'll see each other again.

111
00:05:17,608 --> 00:05:18,693
[in Arabic] God willing.

112
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:20,987
[car door closing]

113
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,780
[ominous music playing]

114
00:05:22,864 --> 00:05:26,659
Boss. The guy delegated by
the Muslim Affairs has arrived.

115
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:29,787
He's trying to uncover
what happened on the island.

116
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:33,207
But don't worry.

117
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:36,002
I'll deal with him.

118
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:40,048
Before he discovers the truth…

119
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:44,927
[ominous music continues]

120
00:05:47,055 --> 00:05:48,097
[sim card snapping]

121
00:05:48,181 --> 00:05:51,392
[breathing deeply]

122
00:05:52,769 --> 00:05:57,899
[music swelling]

123
00:05:57,982 --> 00:06:00,276
[music fading]

124
00:06:00,359 --> 00:06:06,157
- [engine rumbling]
- [siren wailing]

125
00:06:08,034 --> 00:06:09,535
- [gear shift cranks]
- [car door opens]

126
00:06:12,288 --> 00:06:13,206
[car door closes]

127
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:17,251
- [glum music playing]
- [heavy footsteps]

128
00:06:17,335 --> 00:06:18,503
What happened here?

129
00:06:18,586 --> 00:06:21,047
[Paramedic] Colonel Del Mundo
committed suicide.

130
00:06:21,130 --> 00:06:27,053
[glum music continues]

131
00:06:45,488 --> 00:06:46,489
COL. LUIS DEL MUNDO FOUND DEAD
IN OWN HOME

132
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:47,657
FOUL PLAY RULED OUT.

133
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:49,700
[Sean] This is crazy. I can't believe it.

134
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:53,746
I feel so bad for Colonel's family.

135
00:06:54,330 --> 00:06:56,666
[Jeffrey] Me too. I wonder why he did it.

136
00:07:00,128 --> 00:07:01,587
[Emil] Have you heard about what happened?

137
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:05,800
I didn't think Colonel Del Mundo
could do that.

138
00:07:06,843 --> 00:07:08,678
I went to his house last night, sir.

139
00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:11,848
I was about to question him.

140
00:07:12,432 --> 00:07:13,891
What for?

141
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:15,226
Sir.

142
00:07:15,309 --> 00:07:18,396
He prepared the data
and intel about Datu Rahman.

143
00:07:18,479 --> 00:07:20,064
This is not suicide, sir.

144
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:23,192
What the hell are you saying, Reyes?

145
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:24,777
Sir, don't you see?

146
00:07:24,861 --> 00:07:26,779
They're killing everyone involved!

147
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:31,325
This is the work of someone
sabotaging our operations.

148
00:07:33,244 --> 00:07:35,705
Man, this is heartbreaking.

149
00:07:37,790 --> 00:07:39,625
I'll miss the Colonel.

150
00:07:39,709 --> 00:07:41,210
[chuckles]

151
00:07:42,044 --> 00:07:43,671
Sir, please listen to me.

152
00:07:43,754 --> 00:07:47,175
I've had enough with all your
hunches, Reyes!

153
00:07:47,258 --> 00:07:48,634
Just stop!

154
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:53,973
Instead of finding out why
Datu Rahman was arrested,

155
00:07:54,056 --> 00:07:56,517
why not just look for him yourself.

156
00:07:56,601 --> 00:07:58,769
Isn't that your assignment?

157
00:07:58,853 --> 00:08:00,563
If I were you,

158
00:08:00,646 --> 00:08:03,316
I'd start forming the new Task Force Alpha

159
00:08:03,399 --> 00:08:06,068
so you can catch all those criminals!

160
00:08:06,152 --> 00:08:07,945
What's taking you so long?

161
00:08:08,029 --> 00:08:09,947
I am doing it, sir.

162
00:08:11,199 --> 00:08:13,659
I have several candidates.
I'm currently narrowing it down.

163
00:08:13,743 --> 00:08:15,203
[Emil] Hurry up!

164
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:17,997
We need to catch Datu Rahman
as soon as possible!

165
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:21,626
Muslim Affairs has already
sent a babysitter!

166
00:08:21,709 --> 00:08:23,419
I wonder what else they'll send

167
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:26,297
if Datu Rahman starts
causing trouble again!

168
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:27,548
This is embarrassing!

169
00:08:28,799 --> 00:08:30,635
But it's crazy, isn't it?

170
00:08:30,718 --> 00:08:32,845
We never know what's actually going on

171
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:34,597
in people's lives and…

172
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:36,265
the things they're dealing with.

173
00:08:36,349 --> 00:08:39,352
You'd assume that they're doing great.

174
00:08:40,019 --> 00:08:41,229
But in reality…

175
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,148
they're already crying inside.

176
00:08:46,359 --> 00:08:47,818
I wonder what he's going through.

177
00:08:47,902 --> 00:08:50,821
[grim music playing]

178
00:08:51,906 --> 00:08:56,827
[crying]

179
00:08:58,329 --> 00:08:59,956
If I do this…

180
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:02,208
you need to leave my family alone.

181
00:09:03,251 --> 00:09:06,712
[breathes shakily]

182
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:11,717
[suspenseful music playing]

183
00:09:17,974 --> 00:09:18,849
- [gunshots]
- [body thuds]

184
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:20,977
[gun clatters]

185
00:09:25,898 --> 00:09:30,319
[suspenseful music continues]

186
00:09:52,967 --> 00:09:54,343
Sir, as I mentioned,

187
00:09:55,136 --> 00:09:57,597
there is a strong possibility
that Datu Rahman

188
00:09:57,680 --> 00:09:59,807
isn't behind these murders.

189
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:01,934
Please listen to me, sir!

190
00:10:02,018 --> 00:10:04,645
That's why you should look for him!

191
00:10:04,729 --> 00:10:06,564
So we can settle this once and for all!

192
00:10:06,647 --> 00:10:12,778
[tense music playing]

193
00:10:19,368 --> 00:10:20,911
[MALIK] Those people outside…

194
00:10:21,746 --> 00:10:23,789
I'm really about to lose it with them.

195
00:10:25,207 --> 00:10:26,667
I was just minding my business,

196
00:10:26,751 --> 00:10:29,170
but they kept calling me a terrorist.

197
00:10:30,171 --> 00:10:31,130
[Rashid] They do that to me, too.

198
00:10:31,213 --> 00:10:33,299
Nobody is booking me anymore.

199
00:10:33,382 --> 00:10:36,510
Just because we're Muslims,
that's how they see us.

200
00:10:37,553 --> 00:10:38,971
They dragged all of us into this.

201
00:10:39,055 --> 00:10:43,142
It's because so many people
are being fooled by this video.

202
00:10:43,225 --> 00:10:45,436
I'm pretty sure this is AI!

203
00:10:45,519 --> 00:10:46,562
Fake!

204
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:49,231
[Omar] Absolutely. He wouldn't do that.

205
00:10:49,982 --> 00:10:53,027
I'm just worried about Jamilah and Jalil.

206
00:10:53,110 --> 00:10:54,695
Those poor kids.

207
00:10:54,779 --> 00:10:58,032
They'll surely be affected
by what happened to their amah.

208
00:11:02,912 --> 00:11:04,789
That's why we have
to be there for each other.

209
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:08,209
Especially now that the people
outside are attacking us.

210
00:11:10,211 --> 00:11:11,754
Let's all lean on each other.

211
00:11:12,546 --> 00:11:15,091
Let's not get carried away
by what they say.

212
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:17,968
As long as we know…

213
00:11:18,052 --> 00:11:19,553
we've done nothing wrong.

214
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:20,721
[Norhana] You're right.

215
00:11:27,269 --> 00:11:30,147
[Lara] So you're telling me
that Espina followed you?

216
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:31,273
- Yes.
- [sighs]

217
00:11:31,357 --> 00:11:34,652
Good thing you're finally
picking new task force members.

218
00:11:34,735 --> 00:11:36,862
They could give us a new mission any time.

219
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:38,280
We have to be prepared.

220
00:11:38,364 --> 00:11:39,824
But it's still a tough choice because

221
00:11:39,907 --> 00:11:41,617
there are so many great candidates.

222
00:11:42,535 --> 00:11:44,286
We need to be careful
with the selection process.

223
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:45,955
- Especially now.
- [sighs]

224
00:11:46,914 --> 00:11:47,957
Marcus.

225
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,000
That isn't the only reason
why you're having a hard time

226
00:11:50,084 --> 00:11:52,044
choosing new candidates.

227
00:11:54,630 --> 00:11:56,257
You're having a hard time because

228
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:57,842
you're still blaming yourself
for Oliver's dea--

229
00:11:57,925 --> 00:11:59,718
Lara, stop. Just stop.

230
00:11:59,802 --> 00:12:01,095
But that's the truth, isn't it?

231
00:12:02,096 --> 00:12:03,305
Yes, that's the truth.

232
00:12:04,056 --> 00:12:04,932
Yes.

233
00:12:05,015 --> 00:12:07,351
To this day, I still think about them.

234
00:12:07,435 --> 00:12:09,353
We'll pick new members now.

235
00:12:09,437 --> 00:12:12,523
What if they get killed, too?
How will I tell their families?

236
00:12:12,606 --> 00:12:14,733
Well, somebody has to do the job.

237
00:12:15,317 --> 00:12:17,236
Somebody has to do the job!

238
00:12:17,319 --> 00:12:20,739
We, of all people, know
that this job can get us killed!

239
00:12:20,823 --> 00:12:23,701
Oliver knew that, too,
when he took this job!

240
00:12:24,660 --> 00:12:31,083
[digital trilling]

241
00:12:36,881 --> 00:12:40,676
Lara, those people relied on me.
They were killed unjustly!

242
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:43,304
And I'm telling you, it's not your fault!

243
00:12:43,888 --> 00:12:45,222
It wasn't your fault.

244
00:12:45,306 --> 00:12:47,391
But you can't just replace them!

245
00:12:47,475 --> 00:12:48,767
I know.

246
00:12:49,768 --> 00:12:51,687
But it's time to move on.

247
00:12:51,770 --> 00:12:52,980
Even if it's hard.

248
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:55,608
You have to move on.

249
00:12:55,691 --> 00:12:59,695
[marcus breathing heavily]

250
00:12:59,778 --> 00:13:02,907
[morose music playing]

251
00:13:03,532 --> 00:13:05,117
[digital trill]

252
00:13:05,201 --> 00:13:06,994
ARREST OF DATU RAHMAN
LEADS TO A MASSACRE!

253
00:13:08,037 --> 00:13:13,292
[sorrowful music playing]

254
00:13:18,255 --> 00:13:19,423
[door slams open]

255
00:13:22,593 --> 00:13:24,512
What are you doing here?

256
00:13:24,595 --> 00:13:25,638
[door closes]

257
00:13:25,721 --> 00:13:28,432
[suspenseful music playing]

258
00:13:29,517 --> 00:13:31,644
I'm studying Datu Rahman's case properly.

259
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:33,604
I want to know its root cause,

260
00:13:33,687 --> 00:13:36,273
why the massacre occurred on the island.

261
00:13:36,357 --> 00:13:38,317
You don't have any right
to meddle with that.

262
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:39,235
Marcus.

263
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:42,571
I have the password.

264
00:13:43,948 --> 00:13:46,408
Director Azuela granted me access to it.

265
00:13:46,492 --> 00:13:49,245
Those are my team's files.
You can't just go over them as you please.

266
00:13:49,328 --> 00:13:50,913
Well, would you look at that?

267
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:52,998
I'm already going over them.

268
00:13:53,082 --> 00:13:54,291
Are you doing this on purpose?

269
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:56,544
- Marcus!
- [Azuelo] Agent Reyes!

270
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:00,631
[door closes]

271
00:14:03,217 --> 00:14:04,635
What's going on here?

272
00:14:04,718 --> 00:14:06,387
Sir, I'm just stopping him.

273
00:14:07,596 --> 00:14:09,890
He's meddling with the files of TFA.

274
00:14:09,974 --> 00:14:11,350
Sir, it seems that…

275
00:14:12,643 --> 00:14:14,270
Reyes hasn't been informed.

276
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:17,064
Enough.

277
00:14:17,773 --> 00:14:19,358
I granted him an authorization

278
00:14:19,441 --> 00:14:22,111
to review all those files.

279
00:14:22,194 --> 00:14:25,072
Most especially the operation
on the island.

280
00:14:25,155 --> 00:14:27,366
We don't have anything to hide, do we?

281
00:14:27,950 --> 00:14:29,034
[Marcus] Sir!

282
00:14:29,952 --> 00:14:31,829
Sir, you know this is classified.

283
00:14:32,496 --> 00:14:33,747
[Azuelo] Exactly!

284
00:14:33,831 --> 00:14:36,500
Only those who have access can read it.

285
00:14:37,585 --> 00:14:38,752
He has it.

286
00:14:38,836 --> 00:14:41,589
[tense music playing]

287
00:14:41,672 --> 00:14:42,923
Marcus, please.

288
00:14:43,007 --> 00:14:44,592
That's enough. Let it go.

289
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:45,885
[clicks tongue]

290
00:14:47,303 --> 00:14:49,179
Sir, I'll review it later.

291
00:14:49,263 --> 00:14:51,515
After our meeting.

292
00:14:52,933 --> 00:14:54,393
Meeting?

293
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:55,728
Wait a minute.

294
00:14:55,811 --> 00:14:57,062
What meeting?

295
00:14:57,146 --> 00:14:58,689
We're the ones who's having a meeting.

296
00:14:58,772 --> 00:15:02,735
It's about selecting the new members
of Task Force Alpha.

297
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:05,195
And I'm a part of it.

298
00:15:05,279 --> 00:15:08,115
[tense music playing]

299
00:15:09,825 --> 00:15:11,744
Mayor Josefina wants him

300
00:15:11,827 --> 00:15:14,455
to be involved in the selection process

301
00:15:14,538 --> 00:15:17,541
in choosing the new members of TFA.

302
00:15:18,125 --> 00:15:19,376
I thought,

303
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,711
why not?

304
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:27,635
Sir.

305
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:31,180
Can we talk?

306
00:15:34,808 --> 00:15:35,893
Follow me.

307
00:15:36,685 --> 00:15:37,937
[door opens]

308
00:15:38,938 --> 00:15:42,107
[tense music continues]

309
00:15:42,191 --> 00:15:43,567
[door slams close]

310
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:47,947
[suspenseful sting]

311
00:15:51,450 --> 00:15:52,701
Sir, what was that about?

312
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:55,371
Why does he have to be involved
with choosing members of my team?

313
00:15:55,454 --> 00:15:57,081
I just let him do whatever he wants!

314
00:15:57,164 --> 00:16:00,501
Why do you always let
that Espina get what he wants?

315
00:16:01,752 --> 00:16:03,879
Espina was sent here

316
00:16:03,963 --> 00:16:07,299
because there was a huge failure
that happened!

317
00:16:07,883 --> 00:16:08,759
Oh, I know.

318
00:16:08,842 --> 00:16:11,762
You'll say again that there's a conspiracy

319
00:16:11,845 --> 00:16:14,139
created by people hidden in the dark

320
00:16:14,223 --> 00:16:17,184
to manipulate all of this!

321
00:16:17,267 --> 00:16:18,811
Because it's the truth, sir.

322
00:16:19,812 --> 00:16:21,522
And I know that I'm right.

323
00:16:21,605 --> 00:16:23,983
But at the end of the day,

324
00:16:24,066 --> 00:16:25,567
I wasn't able to stop it!

325
00:16:26,694 --> 00:16:29,488
Me! It's my fault!

326
00:16:30,072 --> 00:16:32,116
That's why I have to put up with Espina.

327
00:16:32,866 --> 00:16:36,829
Because if he reports something
to the higher ups,

328
00:16:38,539 --> 00:16:40,040
I'll be in trouble again!

329
00:16:40,708 --> 00:16:42,251
I'm truly impressed, sir.

330
00:16:43,419 --> 00:16:46,380
By your instincts for self-preservation.

331
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:49,842
That kept me alive all these years!

332
00:16:49,925 --> 00:16:52,803
I've been though countless wars!

333
00:16:52,886 --> 00:16:54,471
Against rebels!

334
00:16:54,555 --> 00:16:57,349
Against terrorists! Syndicates!

335
00:16:59,018 --> 00:17:00,686
So how am I still here?

336
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:02,771
Why am I still alive?

337
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:04,481
Do you know why?

338
00:17:04,565 --> 00:17:06,734
Because when I get showered by bullets,

339
00:17:07,901 --> 00:17:09,653
I'm excellent at dodging them!

340
00:17:10,738 --> 00:17:12,573
I can hide very well!

341
00:17:13,782 --> 00:17:15,743
Did you think I wasn't insulted

342
00:17:15,826 --> 00:17:18,203
when that Espina was sent here?

343
00:17:19,246 --> 00:17:21,040
I was insulted, Reyes!

344
00:17:21,623 --> 00:17:24,752
At my old age,
they're gonna send me a babysitter?!

345
00:17:26,295 --> 00:17:28,088
Why did you agree to it, sir?

346
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:32,634
Because I'm getting showered with bullets!

347
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:36,138
I need to dodge!

348
00:17:36,221 --> 00:17:37,973
I have to get along with them!

349
00:17:39,099 --> 00:17:42,519
Just give this to me. I need this!

350
00:17:43,437 --> 00:17:48,692
[tense music continues, ends]

351
00:17:51,945 --> 00:17:55,157
[ominous music playing]

352
00:17:56,408 --> 00:17:58,744
[Jamilah] <i>Jalil, what happened to you?</i>

353
00:18:01,246 --> 00:18:02,831
Get away! [panting]

354
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:04,291
Get away from me!

355
00:18:04,374 --> 00:18:06,376
- Get away! Stay away!
- Sir! Calm down!

356
00:18:06,460 --> 00:18:07,836
We have to give this to you!

357
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:09,463
Sir.

358
00:18:09,546 --> 00:18:12,674
Sir, we have to do this.
We're not going to hurt you.

359
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:13,801
We're doing this for--

360
00:18:13,884 --> 00:18:15,427
Get away from me!

361
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:16,762
[patient] Stay away!

362
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:18,472
- [nurse] Sir, please calm down!
- [patient panting]

363
00:18:18,555 --> 00:18:20,182
Are you okay, doc?

364
00:18:20,265 --> 00:18:21,558
I'm okay, I'm okay.

365
00:18:21,642 --> 00:18:25,687
- [panting, screaming]
- Sir, please just relax.

366
00:18:25,771 --> 00:18:28,023
We're not going to hurt you, sir.

367
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:30,400
- [patient panting slowly]
- Just take it easy.

368
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:34,655
We won't hurt you. We're here to help you.

369
00:18:34,738 --> 00:18:37,116
No one here is going to hurt you.

370
00:18:37,699 --> 00:18:38,659
[Jamilah] Sir.

371
00:18:39,451 --> 00:18:40,786
Mother Mary…

372
00:18:41,662 --> 00:18:43,163
[patient] Mother Mary!

373
00:18:43,247 --> 00:18:47,251
Okay, just relax, sir.
We'll take care of you. Go ahead.

374
00:18:50,712 --> 00:18:52,172
Just relax.

375
00:18:55,342 --> 00:18:58,303
[soft music playing]

376
00:18:58,387 --> 00:19:01,056
There are five available
positions on the task force.

377
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:02,891
These are the police officers and agents

378
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:05,102
that Marcus and I have selected.

379
00:19:07,312 --> 00:19:09,398
Usman Sabdani.

380
00:19:09,481 --> 00:19:11,400
He is an excellent officer.

381
00:19:11,483 --> 00:19:13,318
We were in the same batch
back at the academy.

382
00:19:13,402 --> 00:19:16,405
But due to bias
against him for being Muslim,

383
00:19:16,488 --> 00:19:18,991
he hasn't moved up the ranks.

384
00:19:21,827 --> 00:19:22,911
A Maranao.

385
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:27,082
Eve Castillo.

386
00:19:27,166 --> 00:19:29,042
Combat expert.

387
00:19:29,126 --> 00:19:31,295
[thwacks, thuds]

388
00:19:36,425 --> 00:19:37,926
Ryan Cruz.

389
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:41,346
Silent but precise and deadly
sharpshooter.

390
00:19:41,930 --> 00:19:44,516
One of the best in his
class at the NLEA Academy.

391
00:19:47,769 --> 00:19:49,897
PO3 Liam Rodriguez.

392
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,356
Combat medic.

393
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:55,027
Specialist in frontline stabilization.

394
00:19:55,110 --> 00:19:56,195
He's a marksman.

395
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:59,281
But his real asset
is keeping the team alive

396
00:19:59,364 --> 00:20:00,908
when under fire.

397
00:20:02,701 --> 00:20:04,494
Andre Flores.

398
00:20:04,578 --> 00:20:06,830
Explosives expert.

399
00:20:06,914 --> 00:20:10,083
In one of his missions,
he was able to detect and neutralize

400
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:12,169
12 rigged bombs.

401
00:20:12,961 --> 00:20:17,341
[stirring music playing]

402
00:20:18,634 --> 00:20:20,886
I would only choose the Muslim candidate.

403
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:28,685
Who asked for your opinion?

404
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:31,063
Marcus.

405
00:20:31,146 --> 00:20:33,690
[tense music playing]

406
00:20:34,274 --> 00:20:37,945
I want to talk to them before
they join Task Force Alpha.

407
00:20:38,028 --> 00:20:39,529
I chose them myself.

408
00:20:39,613 --> 00:20:42,532
Director Azuelo didn't
even interview them anymore.

409
00:20:43,742 --> 00:20:46,203
I just want to make sure
that the new members

410
00:20:46,286 --> 00:20:48,872
aren't like the ones they're replacing.

411
00:20:48,956 --> 00:20:50,082
What do you mean?

412
00:20:50,165 --> 00:20:53,585
That they wouldn't kill
innocent and unarmed civilians.

413
00:20:53,669 --> 00:20:55,003
- What did you say?
- Marcus, enough.

414
00:20:55,087 --> 00:20:56,546
[Azuelo] Reyes!

415
00:20:56,630 --> 00:20:57,839
Calm down.

416
00:20:58,966 --> 00:20:59,967
[Lara] Enough.

417
00:21:00,050 --> 00:21:01,093
Reyes!

418
00:21:02,135 --> 00:21:03,220
Calm down.

419
00:21:03,303 --> 00:21:04,721
That's enough, Marcus.

420
00:21:05,389 --> 00:21:08,475
[tense music continues]

421
00:21:15,899 --> 00:21:17,317
[papers scatter]

422
00:21:17,401 --> 00:21:18,735
Who do you think you are?

423
00:21:19,695 --> 00:21:21,697
Who do you think you are?!

424
00:21:22,781 --> 00:21:24,449
I know you have a say over our decisions,

425
00:21:24,533 --> 00:21:27,119
but don't you dare
insult our fallen comrades!

426
00:21:28,495 --> 00:21:30,789
Agent Angeles, I am not
insulting your comrades.

427
00:21:30,872 --> 00:21:32,416
I'm just being honest.

428
00:21:32,499 --> 00:21:34,626
- I'm just doing my job.
- [Lara scoffs]

429
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:36,837
You're doing your job?

430
00:21:38,714 --> 00:21:40,048
You don't know them!

431
00:21:41,591 --> 00:21:44,928
You don't know them the way we do!

432
00:21:45,012 --> 00:21:48,223
No wonder Marcus is furious,
even I'm offended!

433
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:50,017
- Did I offend you?
- Yes!

434
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:51,268
- Yes!
- Huh?

435
00:21:51,351 --> 00:21:53,478
What about the people
who died on the island?!

436
00:21:53,562 --> 00:21:55,897
They also had friends, Agent Angeles.

437
00:21:57,774 --> 00:21:59,818
Are you aware that
there were children who died?

438
00:22:01,486 --> 00:22:05,949
Those children had families too.

439
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:08,660
- [Jalil] <i>Run!</i>
<i>- </i>[people screaming]

440
00:22:08,744 --> 00:22:10,662
- Run!
- [gunshots]

441
00:22:10,746 --> 00:22:12,289
Mama!

442
00:22:12,372 --> 00:22:13,665
My daughter!

443
00:22:13,749 --> 00:22:15,500
[gunshots]

444
00:22:17,002 --> 00:22:18,170
[body thuds]

445
00:22:18,253 --> 00:22:21,757
- [gunshots]
- [grim music playing]

446
00:22:24,551 --> 00:22:25,844
[Jalil] <i>Mothers…</i>

447
00:22:28,555 --> 00:22:29,681
fathers…

448
00:22:29,765 --> 00:22:33,060
parents lost their children in an instant.

449
00:22:34,061 --> 00:22:36,271
- [people screaming]
- Oh, no!

450
00:22:36,354 --> 00:22:42,527
- [gunshots]
- [people screaming]

451
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:44,571
Father, wake up!

452
00:22:45,238 --> 00:22:47,407
- Hey!
- Help me!

453
00:22:48,325 --> 00:22:51,036
[coughing]

454
00:22:54,164 --> 00:22:55,373
[sobbing]

455
00:22:57,167 --> 00:22:58,335
[Jalil] <i>You're mad?</i>

456
00:22:59,294 --> 00:23:00,504
Hmm?

457
00:23:00,587 --> 00:23:02,255
You said you were angry, didn't you?

458
00:23:03,799 --> 00:23:04,841
I'm angry too,

459
00:23:05,592 --> 00:23:07,719
because what happened
on that island was horrific.

460
00:23:09,387 --> 00:23:12,390
I'm sorry, Agent Angeles,
if I offended you.

461
00:23:13,225 --> 00:23:14,851
But what about the people on the island?

462
00:23:16,103 --> 00:23:18,772
Did you consider how they felt?

463
00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:22,400
Who is going to apologize to them?

464
00:23:22,484 --> 00:23:23,485
You?!

465
00:23:23,568 --> 00:23:26,863
[tense music playing]

466
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:39,251
[door slams]

467
00:23:42,379 --> 00:23:43,463
[thud]

468
00:23:44,840 --> 00:23:50,095
[tense music continues]

469
00:23:56,059 --> 00:23:57,352
I'm okay, son.

470
00:23:57,435 --> 00:24:01,148
Our nurse, Jamilah, helped me.

471
00:24:01,231 --> 00:24:02,983
This is my son, Marcus.

472
00:24:03,066 --> 00:24:05,777
[suspenseful music playing]

473
00:24:08,697 --> 00:24:11,658
[man] <i>Keep your eyes on the prize,</i>
<i>Lara.</i>

474
00:24:11,741 --> 00:24:13,618
This is all for the greater good.

475
00:24:13,702 --> 00:24:16,288
[Felix] <i>The General's orders</i>
<i>still carry more weight.</i>

476
00:24:16,371 --> 00:24:18,456
[Jalil] <i>They wiped out the evidence.</i>

477
00:24:18,540 --> 00:24:20,917
<i>Everyone involved was silenced.</i>

478
00:24:21,001 --> 00:24:22,961
<i>But I know I'm in the right place.</i>

479
00:24:23,044 --> 00:24:26,047
<i>And I'll find out</i>
<i>who is behind all of this.</i>

480
00:24:26,131 --> 00:24:29,634
<i>You really think Azuelo will</i>
<i>let Espina join our missions?</i>

481
00:24:29,718 --> 00:24:31,136
<i>I've done a background check on him.</i>

482
00:24:31,219 --> 00:24:33,638
<i>All of his files are</i>
<i>either redacted or restricted.</i>

483
00:24:33,722 --> 00:24:35,557
I don't understand, Lara.

484
00:24:35,640 --> 00:24:37,934
Who is this liaison from Mindanao?

485
00:24:40,979 --> 00:24:43,023
[man] <i>The new members of Task Force</i>
<i>Alpha.</i>

486
00:24:46,484 --> 00:24:47,527
- Ma'am! Sir!
- Ma'am! Sir!

487
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:49,654
<i>I'll finally get to know all of you.</i>

488
00:24:49,738 --> 00:24:51,406
[suspenseful music ends]
